ğŸ”¹ What is Docker?
Docker is a tool that packages your application (including code, libraries, settings, etc.) into something called a container.

âœ… Think of it like:
A shipping container that holds your app and everything it needs to run â€” so it can work the same anywhere (your laptop, a server, or the cloud).

ğŸ”¹ What is a Docker Container?
A lightweight, standalone unit that contains everything your app needs to run:

Source code

Runtime (e.g., Java)

System tools

Libraries

Settings

ğŸ”¹ Why Use Docker?
ğŸ›  Consistency â€“ Runs the same on every environment

ğŸš€ Speed â€“ Starts up fast

